The paper focuses on developing a system for human-robot communication in a shared space, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data-driven techniques, which could fall under the category of statistical learning (cs.SD).
